\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Acoustic target-RMSE improvement versus lift-to-drag retention. Incidence-only designs generally provide similar acoustic improvement with more favourable aerodynamic proxy behaviour than full-geometry designs. Because the aerodynamic quantities are proxies, the figure should be treated as a screening result rather than a validated Pareto frontier.}}{14}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:aero_tradeoff}{{3}{14}{Acoustic target-RMSE improvement versus lift-to-drag retention. Incidence-only designs generally provide similar acoustic improvement with more favourable aerodynamic proxy behaviour than full-geometry designs. Because the aerodynamic quantities are proxies, the figure should be treated as a screening result rather than a validated Pareto frontier}{figure.3}{}}
